# load data
df <- readxl::read_excel('./data/State_to_State_Migrations_Table_2018.xls', skip = 6)
## New names:
## * `` -> ...1
## * `` -> ...2
## * `` -> ...3
## * `` -> ...4
## * `` -> ...5
## * ...
# remove rows full of NAs
df <- df[complete.cases(df),]
# remove first row
df <- df[-1,]
# remove duplictated state name columns
states_name <- df$...1
df_new <- df[, (names(df) %in% states_name)]
# replace N/A to 0
df_new[df_new == "N/A"] <- "0"
df_new <- as.data.frame(lapply(df_new, as.numeric))
#head(df_new)
df_new_2 <- NULL
for (i in 1:50){
  for (j in 1:50){
    if (i != j){
      df_new_2 <- rbind(df_new_2, c(states_name[j], states_name[i], df_new[i,j]))
    }
  }
}

# head(df_new_2)
# name columns as source, target and count
colnames(df_new_2) <- c("source","target","count")
df_new_2 <- as.data.frame(df_new_2)

So now the extracted data is in the form of a data frame with 3 columns: source, target and count:

head(df_new_2)
##        source  target count
## 1      Alaska Alabama   419
## 2     Arizona Alabama  1915
## 3    Arkansas Alabama  1051
## 4  California Alabama  2659
## 5    Colorado Alabama  1672
## 6 Connecticut Alabama   747

Choose four source states: New York, Texas, Pennsylvania, Massachusetts

top10 <- NULL
df_new_2["count"] <- lapply(df_new_2["count"],as.numeric)

ny <- df_new_2[df_new_2['source'] == "New York",]
ny <- ny[order(-ny$count),]
top10 <- rbind(top10, head(ny, 10))

tx <- df_new_2[df_new_2['source'] == "Texas",]
tx <- tx[order(-tx$count),]
top10 <- rbind(top10, head(tx, 10))

pa <- df_new_2[df_new_2['source'] == "Pennsylvania",]
pa <- pa[order(-pa$count),]
top10 <- rbind(top10, head(pa, 10))

ma <- df_new_2[df_new_2['source'] == "Massachusetts",]
ma <- ma[order(-ma$count),]
top10 <- rbind(top10, head(ma, 10))
graph <- as_tbl_graph(top10)
graph <- graph %>%
  activate(nodes) %>%
  mutate(
    title = str_to_title(name),
    label = str_replace_all(title, " ", "\n")
    )
thm <- theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
     axis.title = element_blank(),
     axis.text = element_blank(),
     panel.grid = element_blank(),
     panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
  ) 

theme_set(thm)
# plot the graph
ggraph(graph) +
  geom_edge_arc(aes(width=count, color = from), 
                alpha =0.6,
                arrow = arrow(length = unit(0.1, 'inches'))) +
  geom_node_text(aes(label = label, color = label)) +
  geom_node_point(color="gray50")
